    Scope and Contents
Golab, Czechoslovakian immigrant, recalls the violence between the Progressive Miners of America and the United Mine Workers Union during the 1930's. He also discusses mine working conditions, equipment and procedures, jobs at the mines, and the 1933 strike by members of the U.M.W. 1 tape, 65 mins., 27 pp. 
Interview by Dean Campbell, 1971 
